The whole purpose is to confess, seek penance, and forgiveness, redemption, absolution. To come clean about the "sins" of the self (wrongs that they've done or felt to THEMSELVES), show awareness and due diligence in accountability (of and to self), finding forgiveness of/from self (and/or from the public), in order to seek peace, strengthened will, reparations in relationships, family ties, and overall knowing the self (one's own identity). I.e., More better knowing, awareness, forgiving, and loving yourself, after going or having gone through dark times (intentionally or otherwise).  These songs aren't necessarily just for the public, directed toward others, or for entertainment purposes -- they are downright personal, like journals or diaries, that are about THEMSELVES! and directed to or ADDRESSING THEIR SELVES .. to achieve self awareness, do self evaluation, find redemption. through CATHARTIC CONFESSION. via semi-satirical art/song/music/expression.
